Activity Name: 4th Place | USATF Club Cross Country Championships
Description: Long course. Mud tears. Hay bales. Gnarly winds. And a whole lotta fun! According to the average of the first 31 people that Mark  Huizar ran with, the course was 6.45 miles with 219 feet of gain. Would put me at 4:56.9 per mile. Coming in to the last 100m I was going the same pace as the lapped runners through the mud‚Ä¶ goes to show how difficult it was to traverse. All that being said, I think I raced really well except I let some people slow me down in the first 1k or so. The last 4k I was trying to surge and use the dry patches to catch up to 2nd and 3rd but we just kept accordion-ing. Huge thanks to coach Alize Hartke , supporters unique hartke and others, and teammates Benjamin Holland , Erik Luu , and Moi Martinez for coming out despite some horrendous course conditions. Hope everyone had as much fun as I did!
